candidates.title: Convert elf2tab into a lib+bin crate
candidates.body:
The rationale for this change is to allow cargo-raze to process this
crate as a dependency.  As a bin-only crate, cargo-raze requires
the crate to be published at crates.io and does not permit using a
git repo as the source.

As a bin+lib crate, there is no such restriction.

Signed-off-by: Chris Frantz <cfrantz@google.com>

candidates.title: Add kernel version header implementation
candidates.body: This PR adds the `KernelVersion` header implementation defined in https://github.com/tock/tock/pull/2669.

candidates.title: Update to 2018 edition
candidates.body:
# Summary

This PR updates elf2tab to the 2018 edition. Only the imports have been amended to match new "path clarity" changes.

candidates.title: Update structopt to 0.3.14
candidates.body:
This:
1. Changes the version of structopt to 0.3.14 and makes the necessary updates to match the new API. The motivation for this is upcoming changes for `--fixed-addresses` and the need to be able to parse binary addresses.
2. Removes the help string from the usage string, which prevents help from being printed twice when running `--help` and is easier to maintain.

candidates.title: Update package manifest with correct repo url
candidates.body: Clicking the `Repository` link at https://crates.io/crates/elf2tab should bring you to this repo, and not the main Tock repo.

candidates.title: Update the elf2tab version in Cargo.lock.
candidates.body: As-is, building elf2tab with `cargo build` causes `cargo` to update this version number, leaving a local change in the elf2tab repository. This change lets us run `cargo build` without generating local changes.

candidates.title: Minor improvements
candidates.body:
Some minor improvements for performance and readability!

I haven't tested the `s/write!/writeln!` but I think the code becomes easier to read!
